org.jsapar.schema

Class SchemaCellFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.schema.SchemaCellFormat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class SchemaCellFormat
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    Describes the format of a cell when converted to or from text, including what data type that the cell is expected to have.

    When creating an instance of this class you may choose to add a Format or a pattern and optionally a Locale. The pattern has different meaning depending on the data type:

    • When the data type is of type String, the pattern is a regular expression as described in Pattern to validate against.
    • When the data type is of a numerical type, the pattern is the same as described in DecimalFormat
    • If the type is boolean, the pattern should contain the true and false values separated with a ; character. Example: pattern="Y;N" will imply that Y represents true and N to represents false. Comparison while parsing is not case sensitive. Multiple true or false values can be specified, separated with the | character but the first value is always the one used while composing. Example: pattern="Y|YES;N|NO"
    • If the type is of a date or time type, the pattern should be described according to SimpleDateFormat
